a target they had touched compared to when they moved their arm to the target location without touching it.}{\fs20\expnd-1\expndtw-3
 A slightly different approach revealed that participants made more accurate and more consistent reaches with the index finger on one hand to the unseen index finger on the other hand, when a brief vibrotactile stimulus was applied to the target index finger (Mikula et al., 2018).}
